  "texts": [
    "By fitting this scaling law inside the QLRO ⊕ Z 2 NM phase in the bottom panel of Fig. 7, we verify that this phase is described by a CFT with c = 1.",
    "Furthermore, we note that in the dual system, Z q symmetry remains unbroken.",
    "However, the spatial Z 2 symmetry between the sublattices can still break.",
    "When analyzed using isotropic CTMRG, this Z 2 breaking results in an additional log 2 contribution to the EE in the nematic phases, as the boundary MPS obtained from isotropic CTMRG is an equal superposition of the two ordered states.",
    "On the other hand, in Fig. 1(g) of the main text, we present the EE for the dual system computed using anisotropic CTMRG with a 2 × 2 unit cell."
